"Deus lo volt" was the battle-cry of the [[The Crusades|Crusaders]]. It means "God wills it" in [[Lingua franca|Lingua Franca]], an international language (similar to some degree to the modern [[Interlingua]]) of Western Europe. "Deus" is Latin for God. "Lo" is Italian for "it." "Volt" is third person singular for the Medieval French verb Voler - to will, wish, desire, want.


